Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest list

Purpose:
  List archive objects as a bounded, pageable collection.

Usage:
  spinedigest list <archive.sdpub> [--id <ids>] [--chapter <ids>] [--type <types>] [--order <doc-asc|doc-desc>] [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json]

Contract:
  - Mutates: no.
  - LLM: no.
  - Types: chapter, summary, node, fragment, sentence, meta.
  - Scope: `--chapter 12` or `--chapter 11,12` limits chapter-owned objects.
  - IDs: `--id node:1,node:2,chapter:12` returns matching collection items.
  - Order: `doc-asc` or `doc-desc`; default `doc-asc`.
  - Pagination: default `--limit 20`; pass returned `nextCursor` back with `--cursor`.
  - JSON: yes.

Use `page` when you already know one object id and need the detailed page.

Examples:
  spinedigest list book.sdpub --type chapter
  spinedigest list book.sdpub --type node --chapter 12 --json
  spinedigest list book.sdpub --id node:320,fragment:13:0 --json
